725020f-b.title: Queens: 14th Avenue - 117th Street
725020f-b.text:
14th Avenue, at the N.E. corner of 117th Street, showing two
views of a late nineteenth century private home. It was owned in
1873 by J. H. Rauch and in 1891 by O. Roesingle. 14th Avenue,
here, was then known as First Avenue.
P. L. Sperr  March 13, 1932
NO REPRODUCTIONS  Views 1,2
